data.title: When Bollywood Actress Manisha Koirala's Name Was Linked To These Celebs
data.meta_description: Manisha tied the knot with business tycoon Samrat Dahal in 2010.
data.text:
Bollywood actress Manisha Koirala is currently in the limelight for her performance in Heeramandi. Released on Netflix, the series is directed by Sanjay Leela Bhansali. Manisha plays a pivotal role in it. She was born into the politically prominent Koirala family in Nepal. She made her acting debut with the Nepali film Pheri Bhetaula in 1989 and went on to feature in the Hindi drama Saudagar in 1991. Since then, the actress has never looked back and has continued her journey. She worked in popular movies like 1942: A Love Story, Bombay, Mann, Lajja, and Mehbooba, to name a few. Till now, Manisha Koirala has worked in more than 89 films and series. Manisha Koirala has also been in the news more for her personal life. Her alleged affairs had always grabbed limelight. Today, let’s take a look at the actress’ love life.

According to reports, Manisha’s name was linked with Vivek Mushran, the hero of her debut film Saudagar. A lot of headlines kept coming out about their relationship. This didn’t last long and they decided to part ways.

Around this time DJ Whosane entered Manisha’s life. Reports claimed that DJ Whosane even proposed to Manisha for marriage, but she didn’t agree. After her split with DJ Whosane, Manisha reportedly fell for a London-based Nigerian businessman.

There were also reports of her dating an Australian diplomat in Nepal. Manisha Koirala’s name was also linked with music director Sandeep Chowta.

Manisha tied the knot with Samrat Dahal – a business tycoon who was seven years younger to her — in 2010. They got divorced after two years of marriage in 2012.
